The open data initiative in Bulgaria (1) is mostly government-led and dates back to 2014 and the transposition of the no longer in force Directive 2013/37/EU of the European Parliament and of the Council of 26 June 2013 amending Directive 2003/98/EC on the re-use of public sector information.(2) Under the Electronic Government Act (EGA) (3) and the Access to Public Information Act (APIA) (4) the Chairman of the State eGovernment Agency has the leading role in the field of public sector information in machine-readable open format and powers related to activities such as:
•	conducting the state policy in the field of information from the public sector in machine-readable open format (Art. 7c, para 1f of the EGA);
•	issuing methodological instructions and assisting the administrations in defining the structure and content of the data sets for publication in the open data portal under the Access to Public Information Act (Art. 7c, para 2, item 19 of the EGA);
•	control over the availability of automated interfaces for ensuring free public access to electronic documents, information and data in machine-readable open format, including by publishing the Open Data Portal, according to an approved template for preparation of technical and functional assignments for public procurement for development, upgrading or implementation of information systems or electronic services by the administrative bodies (Art. 58a, item 2 of the EGA);
•	determination of the metadata of the registers and databases, which support public, free and free interfaces for connected open data by the order of the Law for access to public information (art. 15, art. 1 and para 5 of NOIISREU);
•	assisting the executive bodies for the inclusion in the annual operational plans of goals related to ensuring the gradual publication on the Internet of information arrays and resources, which it maintains in an open machine-readable format, access to which is free. (Article 15b, paragraph 2 of the APIA);
•	proposing for approval to the Council of Ministers an annual list of data sets to be published in an open format on the Internet (Article 15b, paragraph 3 of the APIA);
•	creation and maintenance of an Open Data Portal (Art. 15d, para. 2 of the APIA);
•	preparation every three years of a summary report on the availability of information for re-use provided by public sector organizations, the conditions under which it is provided and the practices for legal protection (Article 16a, paragraph 1 of the APIA);
•	establishment of violations under Art. 15g, para. 2 of the APIA (Art. 43, para. 1 of the APIA);
•	issuance of penal decrees regarding art. 15 d, para 2 (art. 43, para 2, item 4 of the APIA).  
Most of these activities are delegated to the "Data" Department (Отдел "Данни"), "Unified System Integrator" Directorate of the State eGovernment Agency (5).
The Chairman of the Agency issued in 2020 two rules and guidelines on open data - the Methodological instructions to define the structure and content of publishing datasets in the Open Data Portal and updating them (7) and the Rules and procedures in the process of planning, prioritization, publication and updating of public sector information for reuse on the Open Data Portal.(8)

